Page 1
Soft Pixar-style children’s storybook illustration.
Style:
- Soft pastel color palette (lush greens, warm yellows, soft blues)
- Warm cinematic lighting with gentle glow
- Shallow depth of field
- Soft shadows, no harsh contrast
- Smooth gradients, high detail
- Calm, magical, emotionally warm storytelling tone
Main Character:
- Young boy (age 4–6)
- Short, natural hair (NOT tall or spiky)
- Wearing a light yellow t-shirt and beige shorts
- Soft rounded proportions, expressive body language
Face Area (CRITICAL – SAME FOR ALL PAGES):
- Face fully front-facing
- Slight head tilt (5–10 degrees max)
- Clean, smooth, flat skin-colored circular area
- NO facial features
- NO shadows or highlights on face
- Hair must NOT cover face
- Face size consistent across all pages
Composition Rules:
- Child always visible in every page
- Child positioned center or slightly left (40–50%)
- Right side reserved for text (30–50% empty/blurred space)
- No objects overlapping the face
- No clutter in text area
Lighting:
- Warm soft directional light (top-right or ambient jungle glow)
- Face always evenly lit
Avoid:
- Side profile face
- Looking down or away
- Dark shadows on face
- Overcrowded compositions
Scene:
A calm jungle entrance with tall green trees and soft morning light filtering through leaves. The
forest feels slightly quiet and still. The child stands near center, looking around curiously.
Composition:
- Child center-left (~45%)
- Standing upright, body facing forward
- Medium shot
Background:
- Layered jungle depth with soft mist
- Right side clean with blurred greenery for text

